<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="112" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[111,647,1002,1184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="112">DIAGNOSIS. — Shells small to large, relatively thin-shelled, usually white, globose, subcircular, exterior smooth with irregular commarginal growth increments. Hinge teeth absent. Ligament internal either in a groove or laterally inset. Anterior adductor muscle scar generally long and in most species detached from pallial line for at least half of length. Pallial line entire or divided.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
